                              COMMITS

Use concise commit messages that describe one logical change.

Format:

  type(scope): summary

Types:

  feat    A user-facing feature or new capability
  fix     A bug fix
  chore   Maintenance, cleanup, tooling, or structure changes
  docs    Documentation-only changes
  test    Test-only changes
  refactor Code restructuring without behavior changes

Scope:

  Use a short lowercase area name, such as ocaml, go, zed, docs,
  boilerplate, tests, or build.

Summary:

  Write in the imperative mood.
  Keep it short and specific.
  Do not end with a period.

Examples:

  feat(ocaml): add dune project scaffold
  chore(ocaml): update editor tooling
  chore(go): remove go scaffold
  docs(commits): document commit message format

Prefer small commits. If a change includes unrelated work, split it into
separate commits.
